   "source": [
    "# 6.Give an example where the median is a better measure than the mean"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "e16ad55b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# mean - when data is not having outliers - 1,2,3 4,5\n",
    "# median - when data is having outliers - 1,2,3,4,5,100"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "25de2e71",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "When is Median Better than Mean?\n",
    "📌 Core Idea\n",
    "\n",
    "The median is better than the mean when the data contains:\n",
    "\n",
    "outliers (extreme values)\n",
    "\n",
    "skewed distribution\n",
    "\n",
    "Because:\n",
    "\n",
    "Mean gets affected by extreme values\n",
    "\n",
    "Median remains stable\n",
    "\n",
    "🔹 Example 1: Salary Data (Most Common Interview Example)\n",
    "Scenario\n",
    "\n",
    "Suppose salaries in a company are:\n",
    "\n",
    "25K, 30K, 35K, 40K, 45K, 50K, 10,00,000\n",
    "📊 Mean Calculation\n",
    "𝑀\n",
    "𝑒\n",
    "𝑎\n",
    "𝑛\n",
    "=\n",
    "25\n",
    "+\n",
    "30\n",
    "+\n",
    "35\n",
    "+\n",
    "40\n",
    "+\n",
    "45\n",
    "+\n",
    "50\n",
    "+\n",
    "1000\n",
    "7\n",
    "=\n",
    "175\n",
    "𝐾\n",
    "(\n",
    "𝑎\n",
    "𝑝\n",
    "𝑝\n",
    "𝑟\n",
    "𝑜\n",
    "𝑥\n",
    ")\n",
    "Mean=\n",
    "7\n",
    "25+30+35+40+45+50+1000\n",
    "\t​\n",
    "\n",
    "=175K(approx)\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 Mean = 175K\n",
    "\n",
    "📊 Median Calculation\n",
    "\n",
    "Middle value = 40K\n",
    "\n",
    "🔥 Interpretation\n",
    "\n",
    "Mean says average salary = 175K ❌ (misleading)\n",
    "\n",
    "Median says typical salary = 40K ✅ (realistic)\n",
    "\n",
    "Why?\n",
    "\n",
    "Because one CEO salary (10 lakh) distorts the mean\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 So median is better here\n",
    "\n",
    "🔹 Example 2: House Prices\n",
    "Scenario\n",
    "\n",
    "House prices in an area:\n",
    "\n",
    "50L, 55L, 60L, 65L, 70L, 5Cr\n",
    "Mean\n",
    "\n",
    "Very high because of one luxury house\n",
    "\n",
    "Median\n",
    "\n",
    "Around 60–65L, which represents most houses\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 Median gives a better idea of “typical price”\n",
    "\n",
    "🔹 Example 3: Exam Scores\n",
    "Scenario\n",
    "\n",
    "Marks of students:\n",
    "\n",
    "10, 20, 30, 40, 50, 95\n",
    "Mean\n",
    "\n",
    "Higher due to one topper\n",
    "\n",
    "Median\n",
    "\n",
    "Better reflects average student performance\n",
    "\n",
    "🔹 Example 4: Income Distribution (Real World)\n",
    "\n",
    "In countries, a few very rich people earn huge amounts.\n",
    "\n",
    "Mean income → looks high\n",
    "\n",
    "Median income → shows actual middle-class reality\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 That’s why governments often report median income\n",
    "\n",
    "🔹 When Median is Preferred\n",
    "\n",
    "Use median when:\n",
    "\n",
    "Data is skewed\n",
    "\n",
    "Outliers exist\n",
    "\n",
    "You want typical value\n",
    "\n",
    "Data is not symmetric\n",
    "\n",
    "🔹 When Mean is Better\n",
    "\n",
    "Use mean when:\n",
    "\n",
    "Data is normally distributed\n",
    "\n",
    "No extreme outliers\n",
    "\n",
    "You want overall average\n",
    "\n",
    "🔹 Beginner-Friendly Version\n",
    "\n",
    "Think like this:\n",
    "\n",
    "Mean = average of all values\n",
    "\n",
    "Median = middle value\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 If one value is very large or very small → mean gets disturbed\n",
    "👉 Median stays stable\n",
    "\n",
    "So:\n",
    "\n",
    "If data has extreme values → use median\n",
    "\n",
    "🔹 Visual Intuition\n",
    "Normal Distribution\n",
    "   Mean ≈ Median\n",
    "Skewed Distribution\n",
    "Mean → pulled towards extreme value\n",
    "Median → stays in center\n",
    "🔹 Interview Answer (5 lines)\n",
    "\n",
    "Median is a better measure than mean when the data contains outliers or is skewed. For example, in salary distribution, a few very high salaries can increase the mean significantly, making it misleading. The median, being the middle value, is not affected by extreme values and better represents the typical case. Therefore, in such scenarios, median gives a more accurate central tendency. This is why median is often used in income and real estate analysis.\n",
    "\n",
    "🔹 One-Line Memory Trick\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 Outliers present → Use Median\n",
    "👉 No outliers → Use Mean\n",
    "\n",
    "🚀 Extra (Strong Interview Tip)\n",
    "\n",
    "You can add:\n",
    "\n",
    "“Median is a robust statistic because it is resistant to outliers, whereas mean is sensitive to extreme values.”"
   ]
  },
